<figureCitation id="DAA62A5B62249D57EC7AFB17FD95EE9F" box="[545,588,1158,1182]" captionStart="FIGURE 155" captionStartId="116.[151,250,858,881]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,187,838]" captionTargetId="figure-58@116.[151,1436,159,885]" captionTargetPageId="116" captionText="FIGURE 155. One of three equally parsimonious trees showing the relationships between species in the L. furcatus species group. Character state changes are indicated on each branch by a black bar. Uniquely derived synapomorphies are indicated in bold and with an asterisk." pageId="69" pageNumber="70">155</figureCitation>
